":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":55,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Adam Simon Welsch was born in 1400, in Little Sodbury, Gloucestershire, England, his father, Sir John Simon Le'Walsh, was 25 and his mother, Elizabeth Alice De Ward, was 28. He had at least 1 son with Julianna De'Pontlarch."},"et":{"1400–":"1400–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1407–Male":"1407–Surnud","1407–Female":"1407–Surnud","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1375–1400":"1375–1400","1372–Female":"1372–Surnud","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1372":"1372","1407":"1407","Little Sodbury, Gloucestershire, England":"Little Sodbury, Gloucestershire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–":"1400–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1407–Male":"1407–Kuollut","1407–Female":"1407–Kuollut","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1375–1400":"1375–1400","1372–Female":"1372–Kuollut","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1372":"1372","1407":"1407","Little Sodbury, Gloucestershire, England":"Little Sodbury, Gloucestershire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1400–":"1400–Décédé","1400–Male":"1400–Décé